Analysis for Luminary Page 1
1.Introduction
The document serves as an analysis for Luminary, an educational platform aimed at optimizing the
learning experience for high school students.
1.1.Purpose
The purpose of Analysis document is to outline the scope and requirements for the Luminary
project, an educational platform designed to optimize the learning experience for high school
students. Luminary aims to integrate technologies, including Generative AI and gamification
elements, to optimize learning outcomes and promote student engagement. The document
encompasses the design, development, testing, deployment, and maintenance of the Luminary
platform, with a focus on enhancing the learning experience for students through personalized
learning materials, performance analysis, and interactive features. By delineating the scope of the
project and objectives, the document serves as a roadmap for the development team and
stakeholders, ensuring alignment with the project's goals and objectives.
1.2.Document Conventions
The Analysis Document follows the IEEE Recommended Practice for Software Requirements
Specifications. The following typographical conventions are used:
Section Headings and Subsections
• Main sections are formatted in bold and larger font to stand out and indicate major topics such
as Introduction, Requirements, and References.
• Subsections are numbered (e.g., 1.1, 1.2) to indicate their relation to broader sections and are
used to break down information into specific topics.
Lists
• Bulleted Lists: Used for non-sequential information where the order of items does not imply
priority, such as listing types of user interfaces or features.
• Numbered Lists: Used for sequential instructions or when the order of items is important, such
as steps in a process or prioritized requirements.
Formatting
• Bold is used for all headings and subheadings to delineate sections clearly.
• Italic is employed for emphasis on new or important terms and for titles of documents or works.

1.4.Product Scope
Luminary is an educational platform that uses artificial intelligence to personalize learning
experiences for students. The platform enables users to upload questions, receive customized
practice questions based on their errors, and manage their learning tasks. The platform aims to
improve student outcomes by providing tailored support and remedial tasks for those performing
below a set threshold. The platform supports multiple languages and ensures privacy and data
protection, making it accessible and secure for students from diverse backgrounds. Luminary seeks
to enhance learning efficiency and engagement through its innovative use of technology in
education.

2.Overall Description
2.1.Product Perspective
Luminary is an educational platform conceptualized as a standalone product aimed at transforming
how students engage with and understand educational content through a personalized and AI-driven
interface. This platform is not a part of an existing product family nor a direct replacement for an
existing system, but rather a new venture designed to integrate various functionalities that cater to
the diverse needs of its users. The product facilitates user interaction through its main
functionalities.

The system, as visualized in the provided UML Context Diagram, shows the interconnectivity
between these components and the external interfaces such as users and educational content
provider.

2.2.Product Functions
•
The platform allows new users to register by providing personal information such as name,
email, and username.
•
User inputs are validated to ensure data accuracy and completeness.
•
User registration details are securely stored in a database.
•
The platform provides a login interface for registered users to access their accounts.
•
User credentials (username and password) are authenticated to grant access.
•
Security measures like password hashing and encryption are implemented to protect user data.
•
The platform offers a "Forgot Password" option on the login page to assist users in resetting
their passwords.
•
User verification methods like email verification or security questions are provided to confirm
identity.
•
Users can securely reset their passwords and regain access to their accounts.
•
The platform enables students to analyze their performance and identify strengths and
weaknesses.
•
An AI-powered question analysis system is implemented to understand the context of erroneous
questions.
•
Students can select the number of questions and difficulty level they want to solve, with
customized question sets generated accordingly.
•
Student performance is evaluated based on the percentage of correct answers.
•
A success threshold (e.g., 75%) is set to determine student success.
•
Feedback is provided to students on their performance, highlighting areas for improvement.
•
The platform offers a dedicated "My Tasks" section for students to view and manage assigned
tasks.
•
Tasks related to incorrectly answered questions are suggested for further practice.
•
Students can assign tasks to themselves for additional practice and learning.
•
A "Daily Work" option allows students to engage in regular learning activities.
•
Students can upload PDF files (limited to 5 pages) in the "My Documents" section.
•
File size validation and error handling are implemented for oversized files.
•
The platform includes a feature to access Ministry of Education resources for studying specific
subjects.
•
Approved educational materials provided by the Ministry of National Education are integrated
into the platform.
•
Students can explore and utilize these resources to enhance their understanding and knowledge.
•
A history section allows students to review previously uploaded incorrect questions.
•
Students can revisit and understand topics they previously struggled with.
•
Performance history is accessible for tracking progress over time.
•
An interactive map of Turkey is incorporated into the platform.
•
Users can click on regions for detailed information.
•
Regions are color-coded based on types of questions uploaded by students.
•
Additional statistics and visualizations related to question uploads are provided.
•
A comprehensive user manual ("How To?") is included within the platform.
•
All functionalities and features are covered in detail with step-by-step instructions.
•
Illustrations, screenshots, or video tutorials are provided to enhance user comprehension.

2.3.User Classes and Characteristics
Students
•
Frequency of Use: Regular, possibly daily or weekly.
•
Product Functions Used: Primarily focused on accessing educational materials, completing
tasks, analyzing performance, and accessing supplementary resources.
•
Technical Expertise: Varied, but generally not highly technical. Familiarity with basic computer
operations and web navigation.
•
Educational Level: High school or higher education level.
•
Experience: Users may range from tech-savvy individuals to those less familiar with online
platforms, depending on age and background.
Administrators
•
Frequency of Use: Regular, but less frequent than students.
•
Product Functions Used: Overseeing system functionality, managing user accounts, monitoring
system performance, generating reports.
•
Technical Expertise: Moderate to high technical expertise, including knowledge of system
administration tools and procedures.
•
Educational Level: Typically higher education level with relevant administrative experience.
•
Experience: Experienced with educational platforms or similar systems, capable of handling
administrative tasks efficiently.
System Support/IT Staff
•
Frequency of Use: On-demand, as needed for troubleshooting and maintenance.
•
Product Functions Used: Providing technical support, resolving system issues, implementing
updates and patches.
•
Technical Expertise: High technical expertise, including knowledge of programming languages,
databases, and system architecture.
•
Educational Level: Higher education level with specialized technical training or certifications.
•
Experience: Experienced in IT support roles, capable of diagnosing and resolving complex
technical problems efficiently.
Developers/Technical Supports:
•
Frequency of Use: Regular, especially during system development and updates.
•
Product Functions Used: Developing and enhancing system features, addressing technical
challenges, optimizing system performance.
•
Technical Expertise: Very high technical expertise, including proficiency in programming
languages, software development methodologies, and debugging techniques.
•
Educational Level: Higher education level with specialized training in software development or
related fields.
•
Experience: Experienced in software development, capable of designing and implementing
complex solutions to meet user needs.
The most important user classes for Luminary would be Students and Administrators, as they are
the primary users who interact with the platform for educational purposes and system management.
System Support/IT Staff and Developers play crucial roles in ensuring the smooth operation,
maintenance, and development of the platform but may have less direct interaction with the end-
users on a day-to-day basis.

2.4.User Documentation
User Documentation Components for Luminary Platform:
•
User Manual
A comprehensive guide detailing how to navigate and utilize all features and functionalities of the
Luminary platform. It will include step-by-step instructions, screenshots, and explanations for each
section and option available to the user.
•
Tutorials
Interactive tutorials or guided walkthroughs to assist users in understanding key features and
workflows of the platform. These tutorials can cover topics such as registration, uploading
documents, solving questions, reviewing analysis, and using the map feature. Video tutorials can be
hosted on platforms like YouTube or Vimeo and embedded within the Luminary platform for users
to watch and learn from.
•
Known User Documentation Delivery Formats or Standards
The user documentation will be delivered in digital formats accessible through the Luminary
platform itself, including PDF downloads for offline reference. It will adhere to standard
documentation practices, such as clear language, organized structure, and user-friendly formatting
to enhance readability and comprehension.
Analysis for Luminary Page 7
3.System Features
3.1.Login
3.1.1 Stimulus/Response Sequences
Authenticating User Identity
Stimulus: User attempts to access the system.
Response: System provides a mechanism for users to authenticate their identities before
gaining access to the system.
Entering Valid Credentials
Stimulus: User enters valid credentials (username and password).
Response: If the user account exists and the provided password matches the stored
password, the login is successful.
Prompting User to Sign Up
Stimulus: User attempts to log in with non-existent account.
Response: System prompts the user to sign up for an account before proceeding with the
login process.
Providing "Forgot Password" Functionality
Stimulus: User clicks on the "Forgot Password" link.
Response: System provides a "Forgot Password" functionality.
Sending Password Reset Email
Stimulus: User requests a password reset.
Response: System sends a password reset email to the email address associated with the user
account. The email contains instructions and a unique link to reset the password securely.
Resetting Password
Stimulus: User clicks on the password reset link in the email and resets the password.
Response: System directs the user back to the login screen to enter their new password and
login.
3.1.2 Functional Requirements
REQ-1: The system shall provide a mechanism for users to authenticate their identities
before gaining access to the system.
REQ-2: Upon entering valid credentials (username and password), if the user account exists
and the provided password matches the stored password, the login shall be successful.
REQ-3: If the user account does not exist, the system shall prompt the user to sign up for an
account before proceeding with the login process.
REQ-4: In the event that a user forgets their password, the system shall provide a "Forgot
Password" functionality.
REQ-5: Upon requesting a password reset, the system shall send a password reset email to
the email address associated with the user account. The email shall contain instructions and
a unique link to reset the password securely.
REQ-6: After resetting the password, the user shall be directed back to the login screen to
enter their new password and login.

Uploading Wrong Questions
Stimulus: User navigates to the Analyze component.

Stimulus: User accesses the Analyze component.
Response: The system displays a section where the student can choose the number of

Choosing Difﬁculty Level for Questions
Stimulus: User interacts with the Analyze component.
Response: The system displays a section where the student can choose the difﬁculty level for

Identifying Topics of Weakness
Stimulus: User interacts with the Analyze component.
Response: The system identiﬁes topics where the student lacks proﬁciency.
Visualizing Fields of Weakness
Stimulus: User interacts with the Analyze component.
Response: The system visualizes ﬁelds of weakness to the student, possibly through charts or
graphs.
Generating Questions
Stimulus: The user conﬁgures the desired number and difﬁculty level of questions.
Response: The system generates questions based on the speciﬁed criteria.
Directing User to Solve Questions
Stimulus: User initiates the practice session.
Response: The system directs the user to the tab where they can solve the practice questions
and submit answers.
Checking Success Rate
Stimulus: The user completes the practice session.
Response: The system checks the success rate of the student for the generated questions
batch.
Showing Success Popup
Stimulus: User achieves a success rate above a deﬁned threshold.
Response: The system displays an informative popup stating that the user has passed the
success condition.
Analysis for Luminary Page 10
Prompting User for Next Action
Stimulus: User achieves a success rate below a deﬁned threshold.
Response: The system shows a popup asking the user if they want to see new AI-generated
questions or assigned tasks instead.
Applying Gamiﬁcation
Stimulus: The user interacts with the system.
Response: The system gives points to the user who succeeded on the generated questions to
implement gamiﬁcation within the project.
3.4.2 Functional Requirements
REQ-1: The system shall display a section where the student can upload the wrong
questions.
REQ-2: The system shall display a section where the student can choose the number of
questions that will be generated by AI for the student to practice.
REQ-3: The system shall display a section where the student can choose the difﬁculty level
for the questions which will be generated by AI for students to practice.
REQ-4: The system shall identify the topics where the student has a lacks.
REQ-5: The system shall visualize the ﬁelds of weaknesses to the student.
REQ-6: The system shall generate questions with the desired number and difﬁculty level.
REQ-7: The system shall direct the user to the tab where he/she can solve the practice
questions and submit the answers.
REQ-8: The system shall check the success rate of the student for the generated questions
batch.
REQ-9: The system shall show an informative popup stating that the user had passed the
success condition.
REQ-10: The system shall show a popup where the user will be asked if he/she wants to see
new AI-generated questions or assigned tasks instead when the success rate is less than %75.
REQ-11: The system shall give points to the user who succeeded on the generated questions
to practice gamiﬁcation within the project.

REQ-3: The system shall ﬁnd the part that the desired topic explained in detail.
REQ-4: The system shall send a response to the student by explaining the topic referring
how it was taught in each of the MEB books. (9th, 10th, 11th and 12th grade)

4.Other Nonfunctional Requirements
4.1.Performance Requirements
Performance requirements are very important for our project because they affect everything in the
project. The system must work effectively and efficiently. To ensure user satisfaction, the system
must meet these performance requirements. The performance requirements required in Luminary
project are as follows:
4.1.1 Response Time
Response time is crucial for the usability and satisfaction of the project. The project will
provide a smooth usage experience by keeping the response time to a minimum at every
possible point to the user. Feedback to the user should be given quickly.
• Instantaneous feedback is essential for quizzes and exams to maintain engagement and
momentum in the learning process.
4.1.2 Storage
Efficient data storage is critical for the performance of the Luminary platform. The data to
be stored includes user-uploaded content, personalized learning materials, system data and
user information. For this reason, storage management becomes extremely important.
• Questions that users make incorrectly will be kept in the database and user history will be
created from these questions.
4.2.Security Requirements
Since we store users’ personal information their safety must be taken into consideration. Files that
users upload to the system, such as presentations and articles, may contain personal data or
copyright. The platform must comply with copyright and license agreements and warn the user
about this before using or changing the submitted materials.
• User passwords should be store securely.
• We must inform users that we will use the data in the files they upload
4.2.1 External Policies and Regulations
The Luminary platform must comply with policies and regulations, such as data protection
standards and privacy laws, to ensure its security and safety. To maintain user trust and legal
requirements, the user must pay attention to the Privacy Policy guidelines.
4.3.Software Quality Attributes
4.3.1 Adaptability
The Luminary platform must be adaptable to different user preferences, technological
environments and evolving educational needs. It must enable compatibility with different
Analysis for Luminary Page 16
web browsers, integration of new functionality based on user feedback, emerging trends in
education, and changing subject coverage.
4.3.2 Interoperability
The Luminary platform needs to integrate with existing education systems, tools, and
services to facilitate data exchange and collaboration between various platforms. Using
different education systems that we will use on the platform, such as summarizing, asking
questions, and using local education information, will meet this requirement.
4.3.3 Portability
The Luminary platform must be accessible from a variety of devices and web browsers to
accommodate users' different preferences and technological environments. Since it will be a
web-based application, it will run smoothly in many web browsers and many systems. The
most efficient platform to start with will be desktop.
4.3.4 Reusability
Promoting reusability in the development and maintenance of the Luminary platform
enables efficient resource utilization and facilitates the implementation of new features and
updates.
4.3.5 Testability
Thorough testing of the Luminary platform is important to identify and fix any flaws,
vulnerabilities, or performance issues before deployment. Unit tests, integration tests and
system tests should be performed to increase system functionality, security and performance.
4.3.6 Usability
To increase the usability of the platform, there will be a section that introduces the platform
and a frequently asked questions section consisting of issues that users usually have
problems with.
4.3.7 Modularity
Since we will develop the project with micro-service architecture, the project will have a
completely modular structure. If a problem occurs in any area of the project, the entire
system will not be affected and the continuity of the system will be ensured.

5.Pseudo Requirements
• Documentation Standards
The project will follow industry standard documentation for clarity and clarity.
• Version Control System
Since there are many areas and parts to be developed in the project, we will use a version control
system (Git) to edit the source code, track changes and simplify collaboration between developers.
• Backup and Recovery
In order to prevent data loss in case of system failure in the project, regular backups of user and
system data and the code base will be taken.
• Third-Party Integration
The platform will support integration with third-party services and APIs to perform the desired
functions.
• Language Model Integration
The Luminary platform will use an LLM that is eligible to perform natural language processing
(NLP) tasks such as summarizing, question answering, and content creation.
• Microservices Architecture
The project will consist of many micro-services and their communication will be ensured.
• Backend Technologies
Java with frameworks such as Spring and Spring Boot selected to create backend services micro-
services, and Python programming languages will be used for artificial intelligence and LLM
processes.
• Message Brokers
Kafka shall be utilized as message brokers for asynchronous communication between micro-
services.
• Containerization and Orchestration
Docker containers shall be employed to package micro-services and their dependencies into
lightweight, portable units for deployment across different environments.
• Database Technologies
PostgreSQL and MongoDB shall be selected as database technologies for storing structured and
unstructured data.
• Testing Frameworks
Unit testing shall be conducted using JUnit for testing individual components and functions,
ensuring code reliability and correctness.
• Frontend Technologies
Frontend components shall be developed using Angular.js framework for building interactive and
responsive user interfaces, enabling fast and dynamic rendering of content.
